            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation, study, and recitation and contains 30 verses (ślokas) derived from a work called the Aśaucanirṇaya; it deals with the removal of impurities through ritual and recitation. This work derives from a large text known as the Aśaucanirṇaya or the Ṣaḍaśīti.</summary>
